commit.message:
add argument to add/remove x-csp header (#39)

* add argument to add/remove x-csp header

* change argument name and lint talisman_test

* lint talisman following the renaming

* fix test following the renaming
Use Nox instead of tox. (#37)

Minor CSP specific updates. (#36)

* Test CSP headers completely at least once.

* Add an example how to specify the CSP directives as an environment variable.

* Add Python part of example 7.

* Use ordered dicts to make sure policies aren’t reordered.
Fix typo in README.rst (#35)
Release 0.6.0 (#33)
Fix handling policy directives with multiple sources. (#32)

Allow disabling X-Frame-Options headers by passing `None`. (#30)

* Allow disabling X-Frame-Options headers by passing `None`.

* Add test for disabling Frame-Options.

* Use more unittest2 assert methods.

This helps improve the error output, e.g. by showing the collection that was checked by assertIn and assertNotIn.

Allow passing strings for FP and CSP during initialization. (#31)

This fixes the code to match the docstring, allowing to pass strings *and* dicts for the Feature-Policy and Content-Security-Policy headers.
Improve performance of nonce value creation (#28)

Add support for the Feature-Policy Header (#26)

The Feature Policy Header can disallow features on either self the
origin that specifies the policy; '*' resolves to the set of all origins
and 'none' to disable for all origins. The new header is still a draft,
but supported from Chrome 60 onwards the draft progress is tracked here
https://wicg.github.io/feature-policy

Closes #25
Release v0.5.1
Add pytest_cache to gitignore
Defer reading of per-view options (#24)
